1 provisions:
2 (1) The city or town forecasts or experiences a loss in total non-property tax revenues and
3 the loss is certified by the department of revenue.
4 (2) The city or town experiences or anticipates an emergency situation, which causes or
5 will cause the levy to exceed the percentage increase as specified in subsection (a) or (b) of this
6 section. In the event of an emergency or an anticipated emergency, the city or town shall notify the
7 auditor general who shall certify the existence or anticipated existence of the emergency. Without
8 limiting the generality of the foregoing, an emergency shall be deemed to exist when the city or
9 town experiences or anticipates health insurance costs, retirement contributions, or utility
10 expenditures that exceed the prior fiscal year’s health insurance costs, retirement contributions, or
11 utility expenditures by a percentage greater than three (3) times the percentage increase as specified
12 in subsection (a) or (b) of this section.
13 (3) A city or town forecasts or experiences debt services expenditures that exceed the prior
14 year’s debt service expenditures by an amount greater than the percentage increase as specified in
15 subsection (a) or (b) of this section and that are the result of bonded debt issued in a manner
16 consistent with general law or a special act. In the event of the debt service increase, the city or
17 town shall notify the department of revenue which shall certify the debt service increase above the
18 percentage increase as specified in subsection (a) or (b) of this section the prior year’s debt service.
19 No action approving or disapproving exceeding a levy cap under the provisions of this section
20 affects the requirement to pay obligations as described in subsection (d) of this section.
21 (4) The city or town experiences substantial growth in its tax base as the result of major
22 new construction that necessitates either significant infrastructure or school housing expenditures
23 by the city or town or a significant increase in the need for essential municipal services and such
24 increase in expenditures or demand for services is certified by the department of revenue.
25 (e) Any levy pursuant to subsection (d) of this section in excess of the percentage increase
26 specified in subsection (a) or (b) of this section shall be approved by the affirmative vote of at least
27 four-fifths (⅘) of the full membership of the governing body of the city or town, or in the case of a
28 city or town having a financial town meeting, the majority of the electors present and voting at the
29 town financial meeting shall also approve the excess levy.
30 (f) Nothing contained in this section constrains the payment of present or future obligations
31 as prescribed by § 45-12-1, and all taxable property in each city or town is subject to taxation
32 without limitation as to rate or amount to pay general obligation bonds or notes of the city or town
33 except as otherwise specifically provided by law or charter.
