EXPLANATION
BY THE LEGISLATIVE COUNCIL
OF
A N A C T
RELATING TO TAXATION -- LEVY AND ASSESSMENT OF LOCAL TAXES
***
1 This act would allow the city of Providence to levy a tax in fiscal year 2026, in an amount
2 not to exceed seven percent (7%) in excess of the total amount levied and certified by that city for
3 its previous fiscal year. This act would also allow any residential properties located in the city of
4 Providence, except residential properties registered as short-term rentals, to be exempt from any
5 increase in property taxes.
6 This act would take effect upon passage.
